        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 5:21PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 521 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cherry Valley, or 10 miles south of Harrisburg, moving southeast at 5
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cherry Valley, Wiley Crossing, Birdeye, River Front, Landers, Weona
Junction, Weona, Stewart, Colton, Boat Run, Mersman, Bay Village,
Coldwater, Whitaker, Old Weona, Monterey, and Lake Poinsett State
Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
